SUMMARY:Supercharged 2026
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 edition of the Tesla Owners UK national member event w
 ill be bigger and better\, with more driving opportunities and a new locat
 ion to enjoy. This new exciting location will host our Supercharged Centra
 l in the Millbrook Concept 1 building\, with a great space for talks and p
 anel debates\, a big hard surface for our Concours d'Elegance\, children's
  activities and display cars\, and a range of or partners and suppliers at
 tending too. And for the first time\, we have a range of fantastic driving
  experiences to access. Your ticket will include a chance to drive the ico
 nic Alpine Course and the High Speed Bowl\, and if you want to try out the
  acceleration and speed of your Tesla\, you can buy the optional One-Mile 
 Straight add-on. Entry to Supercharged is free for our paid supporters\, a
 nd payable for free and non-members. This will be a family friendly event.
  One ticket is required per car irrespective of passenger numbers\, though
  track access is for the TOUK member only. Please add the additional One M
 ile Straight ticket if you wish to access that optional experience. SUPERC
 HARGED 2026 HIGHLIGHTS • Technical talks and panel discussions • New owner
  sessions • Mini Tesla track for children including our new Mini Cybertruc
 ks • Accessories and merchandise • Great food and drink • Demonstrations •
  Concours d’elegance • Modified Tesla display • Special parking for Model 
 X and Roadster • Driving experiences with your own car • Full Tesla UK pre
 sence with cars and merch and the Cybertruck • Tesla Mobile Service Please
  note all ticket sales are final and refunds will only be given if the eve
 nt is cancelled by TOUK. Important Notes if you wish to take part in the d
 riving experience elements: Access to the driving experiences will be subj
 ect to a number of rules as you might image to ensure your safety\, and to
  make sure all attendees have their opportunity to enjoy the day! By compl
 eting your ticket purchase\, you acknowledge you have red and understood t
 he following: You must have a valid UK licence. (we are checking if EU lic
 enses are acceptable). You must not have anyone under 16 in the car (child
 ren are very welcome at the rest of the event but you must have an adult w
 ith them at all times). No alcohol is permitted at Millbrook. In all cases
  it is the responsibility of the car owner/policy holder to contact their 
 insurer to ensure that the policy they hold does indeed cover the Millbroo
 k driving day. Additionally\, even if a policy has Track day cover do not 
 assume it covers you automatically it is usually a requirement of the poli
 cy that you notify the insurer in advance. Any damage caused to UTAC prope
 rty will be invoiced to the Member. There will be compulsory attendance at
  a safety briefing and you will be required to sign an indemnity waiver be
 fore receiving your wristband that will gain you access to the tracks. If 
 you wish to access the One Mile Straight\, you must already have your driv
 er briefing wrist band\, and then validate your optional ticket with TOUK 
 event control to gain your special second wrist band. We recommend that yo
 u buy this optional ticket with your main entry ticket as we can’t guarant
 ee space on the day. The event is not a track day or MSA approved\, and no
  helmets required. There is no timing and speed limits are applied\, it is
  a driving experience on private roads. Speed limits applied are 100mph on
  the High Speed Bowl and 55mph on the Alpine Course\, that may sound low b
 ut it's very steep and twisty in places. Once you leave the Supercharged C
 entral area\, you must not deviate from the approved routes as described i
 n the driver briefing\, and you must not stop or exit your car unless inst
 ructed to do so by a marshal. All track experiences are managed by UTAC. T
 heir decision is final on all aspects of track and driver safety. If there
  is any dangerous driving observed\, not only will you be ejected from the
  tracks (and no refunds given)\, you put the whole club at risk of using t
 he site in future. You will have a ½ hour slot to enjoy the Alpine Circuit
  and the high speed bowl. If we become oversubscribed this may be reduced 
 to ensure all members get a chance. If spaces are free towards the end of 
 the day\, you may get a second opportunity so do listen out for announceme
 nts\, but we expect the experiences to be popular and we want to ensure al
 l members get a fair chance to enjoy the tracks. Any cars not observing th
 e recommended experience time will be red flagged by the marshals and will
  lose their opportunity to take part in future driving events. If you are 
 taking part in the Concours d’Elegance\, we will be keeping a slot free la
 te afternoon so that you can take part in the driving experiences once the
  show cars are released from the static part of Supercharged Central at ab
 out 3pm. While we endeavour to enable all members with valid tickets who m
 eet the driving requirements to experience the courses\, this will be subj
 ect to availability on the day and priority will be for Supporter Members\
 , and those who have purchased a one mile straight ticket. We do not want 
 any re-enactments of the James Bond Casino Royal crash (which was filmed i
 n the Alpine Course). No dogs permitted on site.\n\nListing: June 27th\, 2
 026\n\nWall clock / source TZ: Europe/London\n\nEvent & tickets (Ti.to): h
 ttps://ti.to/teslaownersuk/supercharged-2026\n\nSource list: upcoming\n\nT
 i.to DTSTAMP: 2026-06-22T14:36:43+00:00\n\nTesla Owners UK: https://ti.to/
 teslaownersuk\n\nClub site: https://teslaowners.uk/
